 Mandriva Linux Security Advisory                         MDVSA-2014:122
 http://www.mandriva.com/en/support/security/
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Package : chkrootkit
 Date    : June 11, 2014
 Affected: Business Server 1.0
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Problem Description:

 Updated chkrootkit package fixes security vulnerability:
 
 The chkrootkit script contains a flaw that allows a local attacker
 to create an executable in /tmp that will be run by the user running
 chkrootkit (usually root), allowing the attacker to escalate privileges
 (CVE-2014-0476).
 _______________________________________________________________________

 References:

 http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2014-0476
 http://advisories.mageia.org/MGASA-2014-0249.html
 _______________________________________________________________________

